result.execSummary:
The defendant Keith Robert Harris was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling AMENDED FROM Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Follow the terms and conditions of current probation.  Meet with medical provider as required and take all medications as prescribed.  Counseling, treatment, services as deemed appropriate by agent, including talking therapy. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations of probation.
